info.description: Build routes and race to connect cities by claiming train lines before your rivals do. The longer your paths and the more destinations you complete, the closer you get to becoming the ultimate railroad tycoon.

info.helpText:
Setup

Players sit in seats. Press the Reset button to begin. A random player will be chosen to go first.

Players will get 4 trains in their hand along the bottom. Trains are automatically sorted by color. They also get 3 ticket destination cards in their hand on the right side. Players can optionally discard one of their tickets by dropping it on the red X. Unused cards are automatically returned to the bottom of the ticket deck.

Gameplay

On each turn, a player must do one and only one of the following:
  1. Draw two (or one if it is a face-up locomotive) trains from the deck or the five face-up cards. Review the rules for the drawing conditions and limitations concerning locomotives. To draw a card, drag it into your hand. After drawing a card from the face-up group, press the Fill button to refill the area. If three of the face-up cards are locomotives, press the Replace All button to automatically discard and refill the face-up area.
  2. Draw three (and keep from one to three) ticket cards. To draw cards, click the Draw 3 button and follow the prompt. Unused cards are automatically returned to the bottom of the ticket deck.
  3. Claim a route by playing tracks between a pair of cities. First, drag and drop the appropriate colored train cards from your hand to the discard holder with the trashcan icon. Then, to play the tracks, drag and drop once track from the area in your seat into one of the colored holders between the cities. The remaining tracks will automatically fill in from your stash. If you make a mistake, drag one track from the holders between the cities back to your hand and the rest will follow.
Usually, the turn indicator on the seat will automatically advance to the next player after one of the above actions is completed. In case the turn indicator is wrong, press the Next button to cycle through the players.

End of Game

When one player's stash of tracks is less than three at the end of that turn, then each player, including that one, get one more turn.

Scoring

Points for claiming a route between cities are automatically calculated and added to each player's score when the route is claimed.

At the end of the game, each player manually checks to see if they completed the routes between the cities on each ticket. If the route was successful, drag the ticket to the green . If the route was not successful, drag the ticket to the red X. This will automatically add or subtract the number of points on the ticket to the player's score. Tickets dropped are automatically removed from the board.

The player with the longest continuous path must manually add 10 points to their score.

Make any adjustments to the score by using the +/- buttons at the seat.
